{"lemma":"ثَدْيَيْ","slug":"ثَدْيَيْ","root":"ث.د.#","root_slug":"ث-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4368","","n4369"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AB%D9%8E%D8%AF%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"breast"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be full-bosomed"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be wettened or moistened, to be madescent, to be baveuse"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From ث د ي (ṯ d y), from Proto-Semitic *ṯdʾ (“breast, pap, teat, mammary”). Cognate with Hebrew שָׁד (šad, “breast”) and Aramaic תַּדָּא (“breast”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4368","headword_ar":"ثَدِىَ","root":"vdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It became moist"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moistened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadiyati AlA^aroDu","text_ar":"ثَدِيَتِ الاَرْضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sadiyat","text_ar":"سَدِيَت"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The land became moistened by much dew"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: mentioned by Yaakoob, who asserts that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the former is a substitute for the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the latter; but is not known. (M.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadaAhu","text_ar":"ثَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He moistened it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vdAhu","text_ar":"ثداهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TT, as form the T, without. teshdeed,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nourished him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TT:) [or the verb in this sense is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vd~Ahu","text_ar":"ثدّاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", for its inf. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tavodiyapN","text_ar":"تَثْدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"feeding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nourishing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["T","K","TT"]},{"entry_id":"n4369","headword_ar":"ثَدْىٌ","root":"vdY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K, &c.) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vidoYN","text_ar":"ثِدْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadFY","text_ar":"ثَدًى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) the first of these is the form most commonly obtaining: (TA:) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mamma;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the chest whereof the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halamap","text_ar":"حَلَمَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is the head; each of the two parts whereof the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamataAni","text_ar":"حَلَمَتَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are the two heads:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Zj in his “ Khalk el-Insán: ”) [and sometimes, but not properly, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halamap","text_ar":"حَلَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone; i. e., the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pap, nipple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mamilla:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoY muqoEadN","text_ar":"ثَدْى مُقْعَدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a breast that is swelling, prominent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"protuberant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qEd","text_ar":"قعد"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that fills the hand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in that art.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and has not yet become folding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K, in that art.:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raDaEa vadoYa A^um~ihi","text_ar":"رَضَعَ ثَدْىَ اُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sucked the breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the pap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nipple, of his mother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IKtt in TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rDE","text_ar":"رضع"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"peculiar to woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common to woman and man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) being sometimes used in relation to a man; (Msb;) accord. to the opinion held to be most chaste and best known by the lexicologists [in general]: (TA:) and is masc.; (T, M, Mgh;) or masc. and fem.; (S, Msb, K;) but most chastely masc.: (TA;) the pl. [of pauc.] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avodK","text_ar":"اَثْدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,] [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avoduYN","text_ar":"اَثْدُىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEulN","text_ar":"اَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vudiY~N","text_ar":"ثُدِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuduwYN","text_ar":"ثُدُوىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vidiY~N","text_ar":"ثِدِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"v","text_ar":"ث"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of the kesr to the letter following, (S,) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vidaA='N","text_ar":"ثِدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vidaAYN","text_ar":"ثِدَاىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sihaAmN","text_ar":"سِهَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^aSobaHati Aln~isaA='u musal~ibaAtK\n                      \n                     \n                        lahun~a Alwayolu yamodudona Alv~udiynaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the women became widowed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bereft of relations, and without their ornaments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in mourning, having woe, pulling the breasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but this is something like a mistake; and it may be that he meant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~udiy~aA","text_ar":"التُّدِيَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and changed the [latter]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the sake of the rhyme. (M.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tujaw~aEu AlHur~apu walaA taA^okulu vadoyayohaA","text_ar":"تُجَوَّعُ الحُرَّةُ وَلَا تَاْكُلُ ثَدْيَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ujorapa vadoyayohaA","text_ar":"اُجْرَةَ ثَدْيَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ingenuous woman will be made to hunger and will not eat the hire of her breasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the prefixed noun being suppressed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bivadoyayohaA","text_ar":"بِثَدْيَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is plain [as meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of her breasts"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: it is applied in relation to a man's preserving himself from ignoble means of acquiring wealth. (Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jud~a vadoYu A^um~ihi","text_ar":"جُدَّ ثَدْىُ اُمِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May his mother's breast be cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a form of imprecation against a man, and used to imply a wish for his separation. (As, L in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jd","text_ar":"جد"},{"kind":"text","text":".) The saying of 'Alee, on the day of his slaughter of the Khawárij,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AunoZuruwA faA_in~a fiyihmo","text_ar":"اُنْظُرُوا فَاـِنَّ فِيِهمْ"},{"kind":"page_break","n":334},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulFA A_iHodaY yadayohi mivolu vadoYi AlmaroA^api","text_ar":"رَجُلًا اـِحْدَى يَدَيْهِ مِثْلُ ثَدْىِ المَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Look ye, for among them is a man one of whose arms is like the breast of the woman"},{"kind":"text","text":"], not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AHdY vadoyayohi","text_ar":"احدى ثَدْيَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as some relate it, was applied to a man who had, in the place of one arm, a lump of flesh upon his shoulder-joint, which lump, when it was stretched, became equal in length to his other arm, and when it was left, returned [to its original form]. (Mgh.) Respecting ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuday~apN","text_ar":"ثُدَيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the dim., whence the surname"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aw Alv~uday~api","text_ar":"ذَو الثُّدَيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", he who holds"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoYN","text_ar":"ثَدْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be masc. [only] says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added because the word [virtually] means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyad","text_ar":"اليَد"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is fem.,] for the man thus surnamed had a short arm, of the size of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoY","text_ar":"ثَدْى"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is indicated by the fact that they also called him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alyuday~api","text_ar":"اليُدَيَّةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or, accord. to Fr, (A'Obeyd, T,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added, in this instance, in the dim., though"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoYN","text_ar":"ثَدْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is masc., because it applies to what resembled the remains ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqiy~ap","text_ar":"بَقِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":") of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vadoY","text_ar":"ثَدْى"},{"kind":"text","text":", the greater part of it having gone, so that it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luHamoyapN","text_ar":"لُحَمْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uHayomapN","text_ar":"شُحَيْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[dims. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laHomapN","text_ar":"لَحْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aHomapN","text_ar":"شَحْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (T, M:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added because the word is regarded in this case as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaDoEapu","text_ar":"البَضْعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the piece, or lump, of flesh]: (Mgh:) some say that it is the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vanoduwapN","text_ar":"ثَنْدُوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA;) but this requires consideration. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","Msb","S","M","T","Mgh"]}]}}